<b><p class = "trav">What are some travel hacks no one talks about?</b></p>
<p>Well surprisingly many people are not Aware about this. I always use this hack whenever I travel on aisle seats. So there is a small button below the arm rest of the aisle seat which you can press to lift it up. Pretty comfortable when you want to get up or just want some more room. The button is located just towards the back end beneath the arm rest.

2. Before traveling anywhere, Search for travel packages online but NEVER Book them. So what to do then?

Browse through the packages and make a note of places of interest and then draft your own itinerary. This excercise would probably take 30 mins but could save you a lot of money! Many a time there are Alot of places or activities in the packages that won't interest you. You could skip those if you are creating a manual one. Also I have found out that if the same travel package you book manually and individually, it's generally much cheaper.

3. Get your communication skills to work : Call the hotel to see if they can Give you a discount. They generally oblige and this way you tend to get more discounts than the one listed on websites and apps!

4. Redundant info but quite useful : While traveling, always wear a shirt /t-shirt with a front pocket. Quite handy to keep your earphones, boarding pass, passport etc. I always make it a point to follow this!</p>
